    <h2>Leslie Cannold</h2>
    
    <p>Dr Leslie Cannold is an author, columnist, ethicist and researcher. In 2005 she was noted as one of <a href="http://www.theage.com.au/news/%20Education-News/Brain-power/200%205/04/18/1113676693627.html">Australia&rsquo;s top 20 public intellectuals</a> and in 2011 she was made <a href="http://www.iheu.org/dr-leslie-cannold-australian-humanist-year-2011">Humanist of the Year.</a></p>
    
    <p>Leslie is an ideas person and a wordsmith. Her voice is instantly recognisable, as is her passion and ideas, which are never predictable and always her own. She excels at making complex issues engaging for every audience &ndash; from students to seniors &ndash; and in encouraging others to find their own power and voice.</p>
    
    <p><a href="/about-me">More about Leslie</a> <br/>
    <a href="/services">More about Services</a></p>

