    baseball cap. She\xE2\x80\x99s donned cheekbones and a dignified navy suit. She\xE2\x80\x99s\r\n\
    learnt her lesson. She\xE2\x80\x99s showed him! Why, she\xE2\x80\x99s turned out to be quite a\r\n\
    remarkable young lady.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    I don\xE2\x80\x99t wish to be mean when it comes to Lewinsky. There\xE2\x80\x99s no doubt\r\n\
    she\xE2\x80\x99s been through a lot. I mean, I would rather die than have the\r\n\
    idiotic things I said and did in my early 20s - sexual and otherwise -\r\n\
    broadcast to TV audiences worldwide in choice snippets and available\r\n\
    verbatim to every geek with a computer. And I know she\xE2\x80\x99s in debt, and\r\n\
    I\xE2\x80\x99m truly glad to see she\xE2\x80\x99s managed to impress the newspapers and\r\n\
    commentators she so desperately needs to sell the book, to make the\r\n\
    millions, to pay the lawyers, to clean up the mess Bill and Monica made.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    But I don\xE2\x80\x99t like being asked to admire Lewinsky, even though being born\r\n\
    and raised in America gives me an unpleasant clarity about why the\r\n\
    American media and public, having spent most of last year eating her for\r\n\
    breakfast, are this year happy to orchestrate her rehabilitation. It\xE2\x80\x99s a\r\n\
    penchant for tell-all confessions followed by true-grit struggle and\r\n\
    redemption, plus a healthy dollop of guilt, that has got Americans\r\n\
    working their way towards a love of Monica that rivals their love of\r\n\
    Princess Di. And the parallel is not incidental.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    One long afternoon in front of the tube is testimony aplenty to the\r\n\
    American love for public confession. Whether it be about goats and\r\n\
    grandmothers, or daughters who sleep with their similarly aged\r\n\
    step-fathers, there is little Americans won\xE2\x80\x99t divulge for Oprah or an\r\n\
    Oprah-substitute, a live audience and a camera that broadcasts to the\r\n\
    global millions at home.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    But simply \xE2\x80\x9Cletting it out\xE2\x80\x9D is no longer the name of the game. After the\r\n\
    successful reactionary and society-wide assault on \xE2\x80\x9Cvictimhood\xE2\x80\x9D and the\r\n\
    \xE2\x80\x9Cculture of complaint\xE2\x80\x9D, Oprah now articulates America\xE2\x80\x99s new focus on\r\n\
    moving women past the \xE2\x80\x9Cwhining\xE2\x80\x9D stage. \xE2\x80\x9CLet it out and do something\r\n\
    about it,\xE2\x80\x9D she now coaches. \xE2\x80\x9COr shut up.\xE2\x80\x9D\r\n\
    \r\n\
    And Monica has done just that. She\xE2\x80\x99s stopped whining, stopped shopping\r\n\
    and stopped looking like she can\xE2\x80\x99t stop eating. And there\xE2\x80\x99s nothing\r\n\
    Americans like more than a success story, although their standards for\r\n\
    success remain tragically low: be thin, be rich and be famous.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    Now if that formula sounds depressingly like the one that endeared\r\n\
    Princess Diana to the Americans, here\xE2\x80\x99s another important similarity in\r\n\
    both women\xE2\x80\x99s self-promotion strategies. Both Monica and Di \xE2\x80\x9Cmade it\xE2\x80\x9D in\r\n\
    that quintessentially female way - through their relationships with men.\r\n\
    Relationships in which they stood by their men until they were so hurt,\r\n\
    so tragically wronged, that they had to let it out. \xE2\x80\x9CI see myself in a\r\n\
    similar situation (to Diana),\xE2\x80\x9D Lewinsky revealed in a recent interview.\r\n\
    \xE2\x80\x9CI was also wronged by a man who said he loved me.\xE2\x80\x9D\r\n\
    \r\n\
    And let it out they did, in surprisingly similar ways. In \xE2\x80\x9Crevelatory\xE2\x80\x9D\r\n\
    interviews in which every question was known and every response and\r\n\
    facial gesture scripted. Interviews in which tears and despair were\r\n\
    importantly paired - not with bitterness but with a stoic determination\r\n\
    to survive.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    OK, so that\xE2\x80\x99s the name of the game, and she\xE2\x80\x99s playing it. But admire\r\n\
    her? Feel for her, maybe. Want it to work out for her in the end, OK.\r\n\
    After all, she\xE2\x80\x99s been through the spin cycle of the well-practised\r\n\
    presidential bimbo-control machine and, as I\xE2\x80\x99m sure Gennifer Flowers,\r\n\
    Paula Jones, Kathleen Willey and Juanita Broaddrick would testify, this\r\n\
    is not a particularly self-affirming experience.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    But if Americans feel guilty about what\xE2\x80\x99s happened to Monica (and what\r\n\
    hasn\xE2\x80\x99t happened to Bill) as a result of their dalliance, they should\r\n\
    stop looking the other way each time another woman tied up with Clinton\r\n\
    reveals not just how trying he finds keeping his pecker in his pants,\r\n\
    but how difficult a time he has understanding the word \xE2\x80\x9Cno\xE2\x80\x9D.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    But spare me the spiel about her \xE2\x80\x9Cself-awareness\xE2\x80\x9D, her \xE2\x80\x9Carticulateness\xE2\x80\x9D,\r\n\
    her \xE2\x80\x9Cpoise\xE2\x80\x9D and the \xE2\x80\x9Cquick-witted\xE2\x80\x9D way she ducks the questions of those\r\n\
    before whom she has placed herself - dollar signs registering\r\n\
    Bugs-Bunny-like in both eyes.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    I would love a woman of my generation to be put in the media spotlight\r\n\
    for all to admire. Someone whose values and behavior somehow capture the\r\n\
    essence and spirit of the women of Generation X as we face the\r\n\
    millennium. There are a number of high-quality candidates out there, but\r\n\
    Lewinsky isn\xE2\x80\x99t one."
