    may still become law. The Liberal government continues to support it on\r\n\
    the grounds that children have a right to a \xE2\x80\x9Cmother and a father by\r\n\
    being conceived into a marriage or de facto relationship involving a man\r\n\
    and a woman.\xE2\x80\x9D\r\n\
    \r\n\
    But are the Catholic bishops and the Australian government really\r\n\
    worried about the rights of children, or those of fathers?\r\n\
    \r\n\
