    Abortion is in the criminal code in many states in Australia, including\r\n\
    the state of Victoria, of which Melbourne is the capital. However, in\r\n\
    1969 the state court ruled that abortion was defensible if the doctor\r\n\
    honestly believed on reasonable grounds that it was necessary to\r\n\
    preserve the woman\xE2\x80\x99s physical or mental health. While this judgements\r\n\
    has resulted in Victorian women having good access to safe termination\r\n\
    services early in pregnancy, it also clearly established abortion as a\r\n\
    medical prerogative, not a woman\xE2\x80\x99s \xE2\x80\x9Cchoice,\xE2\x80\x9D or \xE2\x80\x9Cright.\xE2\x80\x9D Indeed, after\r\n\
    the story of the 32-week abortion was leaked to the press, the Royal\r\n\
    Women\xE2\x80\x99s quickly established an inquiry to reassure the public that they\r\n\
    would be assessing the reasons doctors had for performing the\r\n\
    termination.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    News reports of the complex case at the Royal Women\xE2\x80\x99s - about which\r\n\
    nothing has been heard from the woman herself - have focused less on the\r\n\
    legal aspects of the case, and more on the ethical issues usually seen\r\n\
    to surround late-term abortions: the late gestational age of the fetus\r\n\
    and the seriousness of its predicted disability. While only 5 per cent\r\n\
    of terminations are performed after 14 weeks, around half of these are\r\n\
    done because of potential damage to the fetus.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    My research suggests that while most women see abortion as a moral\r\n\
    issue, they nominate different ethical concerns to the masculinist ones\r\n\
    mainstream academics and journalists glibly presume to be at issue. Such\r\n\
    views equate \xE2\x80\x9Cviable\xE2\x80\x9D fetuses with babies born, and consequently reduce\r\n\
    pregnancy to an issue of \xE2\x80\x9Cfetal location.\xE2\x80\x9D\r\n\
    \r\n\
    Women, not surprisingly, see the relationship between mother and fetus\r\n\
    as meaningful and at the heart of the moral issues that surround\r\n\
    abortion. Many see the pregnant woman as morally obliged to commit as\r\n\
    early as possible either to gestating the fetus and raising the child\r\n\
    that results, or to obtaining a termination.\r\n\
    \r\n\
