    no feminist. The man Moore describes in Abortion Corruption & Cops is a\r\n\
    social justice campaigner. A man whose own deprived upbringing had\r\n\
    alerted him to the ways in which the rich could circumvent harsh and\r\n\
    unjust laws, while the poor were forced to live with - or die from -\r\n\
    their consequences.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    In her new book about women\xE2\x80\x99s stories of illegal abortion, timed for\r\n\
    release to coincide with the screening of Abortion, Corruption & Cops,\r\n\
    Jo Wainer says that having \xE2\x80\x9Ctweaked the tail\xE2\x80\x9D of the State, Bert\r\n\
    suffered its retributive power. In return for having forced a public\r\n\
    inquiry into police corruption and opened the state\xE2\x80\x99s first legal\r\n\
    abortion clinic. Bert Wainer was bankrupted by the Australian Tax\r\n\
    Office, evicted from his medical surgery by a landlady under pressure\r\n\
    from a Catholic bishop, and censured by the AMA.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    Abortion, Corruption & Cops: The Bertram Wainer Story screeed on SBS on\r\n\
    Thursday April 6, at 8:30pm."
