    For me, it\xE2\x80\x99s the latter. But I would feel differently if such a\r\n\
    female-dominated group came into being in a world where men were\r\n\
    struggling to achieve the legal right to choose safe vasectomy, and the\r\n\
    group\xE2\x80\x99s aims were to help men gain control over an issue so critical to\r\n\
    their bodies and lives.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    What matters, in other words, is not that men are involved but how they\r\n\
    are involved.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    Men lack moral standing in the abortion debate-indeed are guilty of\r\n\
    moral arrogance-when they push for control over a procedure they\xE2\x80\x99ll\r\n\
    never have to have because they can\xE2\x80\x99t get pregnant.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    But when men implicitly acknowledge their lesser standing by raising\r\n\
    their voices in support of laws that take away power from their own sex\r\n\
    in order to give it to women, they can feel confident they are doing the\r\n\
    right thing."
