    So where does this Faustian pact leave parents like Karen? Between a\r\n\
    rock and a hard place, which is why I have no problem with them making\r\n\
    whatever short-term decision they feel necessary to protect their\r\n\
    children\xE2\x80\x99s psychological and emotional health. Children should never be\r\n\
    sacrificed on the altar of their parents\xE2\x80\x99 principles.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    But in the long-term Karen, and others like her, must fight. Beat on the\r\n\
    door of the Education Minister until she amends the department\xE2\x80\x99s policy\r\n\
    that prescribes suitable alternatives being provided for kids whose\r\n\
    parents say no to scripture. So that no parent, or child, has to endure\r\n\
    what they\xE2\x80\x99ve had to again."
