    reviled did not encompass women, this seems doubtful when he often\r\n\
    explicitly included them.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    In the sayings and parables most scholars agree can be attributed to\r\n\
    Joshua, we find justice-seeking widows, coin-sweeping housewives and\r\n\
    prudent bakers who know just how to leaven bread so that one loaf\r\n\
    becomes many.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    In the gospel of Thomas, Joshua responds to Peter\xE2\x80\x99s scathing dismissal\r\n\
    of disciple Mary Magdalene as \xE2\x80\x9Cnot worthy of life\xE2\x80\x9D by insisting that he\r\n\
    will \xE2\x80\x9Cguide her \xE2\x80\xA6 for every female who makes herself male will enter\r\n\
    heaven\xE2\x80\x99s kingdom\xE2\x80\x9D. Added to this is evidence that women comprised many,\r\n\
    if not most, of Joshua\xE2\x80\x99s followers. Perhaps among these dignity-seeking\r\n\
    Jewish women was one or more of Joshua\xE2\x80\x99s sisters?\r\n\
    \r\n\
    The truth is that we\xE2\x80\x99ll never know. When I realised so many years ago\r\n\
    that Joshua\xE2\x80\x99s sisters had been cruelly written out of history, and that\r\n\
    no matter how much I cared, I could not reinstate them, I felt useless.\r\n\
    None of the tools I had spent so many years acquiring as an academic\r\n\
    scholar and general audience non-fiction writer were in any way equal to\r\n\
    the task. I was surplus to what these women required.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    I tried to forget the sisters. To abandon them to the dust of the\r\n\
    unmarked past where I\xE2\x80\x99d found them, but failed. To do so made me feel\r\n\
    complicit in perpetuating what they\xE2\x80\x99d already suffered - the terrible\r\n\
    pain of being forgotten.\r\n\
    \r\n\
    There was only one thing left to do. Slowly, I learned the craft of\r\n\
    fiction writing so I could tell these stories the only way they could be\r\n\
    told. By letting my imagination take wing."
