    <p><img align="right" style="padding-left: 10px;" alt="The Book of Rachael cover" src="/static/images/cover-book-of-rachael.jpg"></p>
    
    <p>What if the man you loved betrayed your brother? Two thousand years ago, as a charismatic young preacher from Nazareth was gathering followers among the people of Galilee, his sister swept floors and dreamed of learning to read. In Leslie Cannold&rsquo;s story, it is the women of Nazareth who take centre stage.</p>
    
    <p>The rebellious, gifted Rachael, consigned by her sex to a life of drudgery.</p>
    
    <p>Bindy, the crone who teaches her the skills of the healer.</p>
    
    <p>Shona her sister, the victim of a harsh social code, and their mother Miriame, a woman seemingly unable to love.</p>
    
    <p>When Rachael falls in love with her brother&rsquo;s dearest friend, the rebel Judah of Iscariot, it seems that at least one of the women of Nazareth may find happiness. Then a message comes from her brother in Jerusalem and events begin to unfold that will change not just Rachael&rsquo;s life, but the world, forever.</p>
    
    <blockquote><p><em>&ldquo;Passionate, eloquent and compelling, a terrific idea beautifully realised &ndash; I couldn&rsquo;t put it down.&rdquo;</em></p></blockquote>
    
    <p><em>Liz Byrski</em></p>
    
