  whole_day: "1"
  title: Good and Bad Religion
  submission_notify_name: 
  submission_intro: 
  content_markup: "<p>Leslie is Centre Stage with Dr Peter Vardy and Assoc Prof Zeki\n\
    Saritoprak in a St James Ethics Centre and ISRA co-production.</p>\n\n\
    <p>Religion is blamed for great suffering, oppression, wars and hatred\n\
    throughout history. Many horrific acts have been undertaken in the name\n\
    of religion.Yet, religion at its best has brought out greatness in\n\
    humanity at the individual and social life through expressions of self\n\
    sacrifice, love and compassion. Religion has produced spiritual,\n\
    intellectual and insightful individuals expressing themselves through\n\
    art, literature and science. \xE2\x80\x98Good\xE2\x80\x99 and \xE2\x80\x98bad\xE2\x80\x99 religion seems to exist\n\
    across all religions. Is it the religion or human nature at play? In\n\
    this centre stage discussion, we will explore factors that cause\n\
    religion to be used as a means for excellence or destruction</p>\n\n\
    <p>What: Public Discussion \xE2\x80\x9CGood Religion, Bad Religion\xE2\x80\x9D chaired by Dr\n\
    Simon Longstaff \\\n\
    When: Sunday 6 March, 2011, 5:30pm for 6:00pm start\\\n\
    Where: The Sebel Paramatta, 350 Church St, Paramatta\\\n\
    Cost: $20 per person, includes tea and coffee</p>\n\n\
    <p>More information from Makiz Ansari at\n\
    <a href=\"makiz@isra.org.au\">[makiz@isra.org.au](mailto:makiz@isra.org.au)</a> or\n\
    0431 549 700</p>\n"
